<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="17" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
<taxonomicName LSID="CC6F6F27-FA23-5FD2-87AB-6AC80A0CF1D6" authority="Reitter, 1911" authorityName="Reitter" authorityYear="1911" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Eurymeloe" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Eurymeloe" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Eurymeloe Reitter, 1911</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="17" type="type species">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Type species.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Panzer" authorityYear="1793" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Meloe" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Meloe brevicollis" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicollis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Meloe brevicollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Panzer, 1793 (by subsequent designation of Pinto and Selander, 1970).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="17" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Description (adult).</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
Size small or medium (6-30 mm), usually robust in appearance. Body integument colour black to moderately metallic blue, bright, silky, or with an oily shininess (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Habitus of some living adult specimens of the current subgenera of Eurymeloe A subgenus Eurymeloe Eurymeloe, represented by a specimen of Eurymeloe (Eurymeloe) ibericus from Puebla de la Sierra, northern Madrid, Spain B subgenus Eurymeloe Coelomeloe, represented by a specimen of Eurymeloe (Coelomeloe) tuccia found 3 km east of Celin, Sierra de Gador, Almeria, Spain C-I subgenus Eurymeloe Bolognaia C Eurymeloe (Bolognaia) affinis from the surroundings of Bab Taza, Rif Mountains, Morocco D E. (Bolognaia) mediterraneus (type species of the subgenus Eurymeloe Bolognaia) from Puebla de la Sierra, northern Madrid, Spain E E. (Bolognaia) glazunovi from Istria, Romania F E. (Bolognaia) gomari from the surroundings of Bab Taza, Rif Mountains, Morocco G E. (Bolognaia) nanus from Alcazar de San Juan, Ciudad Real, Spain H E. (Bolognaia) fernandezi from Los Sauces, La Palma, Canary Islands I Eurymeloe orobates sp. nov., from Puerto de la Quesera, Guadalajara, Spain J Eurymeloe (Bolognaia) murinus from Tizi n'Tichka, High Atlas, Morocco. Photographs: A-C, F, G, I (ASV) E, H, J (MGP) D (J. Aznar Gonzalez de Rueda)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1109.83863.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/709032" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">2I</figureCitation>
). Body pubescence very short, recumbent, or absent on the head and pronotum. Head rounded, sides almost straight, convergent to the eyes. Eyes small, subreniform, weakly protruding, and without longitudinal depression behind them. Antennae submoniliform, robust, short or medium in length, usually not reaching the posterior margin of the pronotum, smoothly thickened towards the apex in some species (e.g., 
<taxonomicName genus="E." lsidName="E. brevicollis" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="brevicollis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">E. brevicollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); in males, unmodified. Antennomeres subcylindrical or subconical, V to VII (in some species IV to IX, e.g., 
<taxonomicName genus="E." lsidName="E. brevicollis" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="brevicollis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">E. brevicollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), wider than long or, at most, as wide as long. Clypeus transverse, approximately twice as wide as long. Labrum wide, fore margin broadly emarginate. Mandibles robust, often curved along the outer margin. Pronotum slightly or moderately convex, very transverse, usually more than 1.7 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
wider than long, sides not parallel and obtusely rounded, posterior margin broadly emarginated, posterior corners rounded. Pronotum surface slightly variable, moderately convex, usually with a weak, diffuse, median longitudinal groove. Head and pronotum punctation from fine and scattered, sometimes almost absent, to deep and dense, with or without (
<taxonomicName genus="E." lsidName="E. brevicollis" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="brevicollis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">E. brevicollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) very short pubescence. Hind margin of mesonotum straight or weakly arcuate. Elytra short and dehiscent, smooth to densely coriaceous or rugose. Legs normal, robust, pilose. Tarsomeres without hair pads or dense setose pubescence on the inferior side. Last abdominal ventrite broadly emarginated in males. Male genitalia: Gonostyli moderately short, distal regions wide, usually digitiform in lateral view, rounded at apex; gonocoxal plate broadly widened at the middle in dorsal view; aedeagus robust, relatively shorter than the gonoforceps or, at most, similar in length.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="17" type="taxonomic remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Taxonomic remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
According to the present definition of the subgenus 
<taxonomicName authority="Eurymeloe" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Eurymeloe" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Eurymeloe (Eurymeloe)" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Eurymeloe">Eurymeloe Eurymeloe</taxonomicName>
, it is correlated with the 
<taxonomicName genus="E." lsidName="E. brevicollis" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="brevicollis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">E. brevicollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group defined by 
<bibRefCitation author="Bologna, MA" journalOrPublisher="Fragmenta Entomologica" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="233 - 301" refId="B1" refString="Bologna, MA, 1988. Note su Eurymeloe e revisione delle specie euromediterranee del gruppo rugosus (Coleoptera, Meloidae). Fragmenta Entomologica 20 (2): 233 - 301" title="Note su Eurymeloe e revisione delle specie euromediterranee del gruppo rugosus (Coleoptera, Meloidae)." volume="20" year="1988">Bologna (1988)</bibRefCitation>
. It comprises a heterogeneous group of species characterised mainly by the following features in adults: small or medium in size, with a robust appearance; metallic blue or black body colour; reduced pilosity that is very scarce and short, often almost absent; wide antennomeres with V-VII usually wider than long; and variable head and pronotum punctation and elytral rugosity (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Bologna, MA" journalOrPublisher="Fragmenta Entomologica" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="233 - 301" refId="B1" refString="Bologna, MA, 1988. Note su Eurymeloe e revisione delle specie euromediterranee del gruppo rugosus (Coleoptera, Meloidae). Fragmenta Entomologica 20 (2): 233 - 301" title="Note su Eurymeloe e revisione delle specie euromediterranee del gruppo rugosus (Coleoptera, Meloidae)." volume="20" year="1988">Bologna 1988</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bologna, MA" journalOrPublisher="Biogeographia" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" refId="B3" refString="Bologna, MA, 1991. Fauna d'Italia. XXVIII. ColeopteraMeloidae. Ed. Calderini, Bologna. [i-xiv] 541 pp." title="Fauna d'Italia. XXVIII. ColeopteraMeloidae. Ed. Calderini, Bologna. [i-xiv] 541 pp." year="1991">1991</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
<bibRefCitation author="Bologna, MA" journalOrPublisher="Fragmenta Entomologica" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="233 - 301" refId="B1" refString="Bologna, MA, 1988. Note su Eurymeloe e revisione delle specie euromediterranee del gruppo rugosus (Coleoptera, Meloidae). Fragmenta Entomologica 20 (2): 233 - 301" title="Note su Eurymeloe e revisione delle specie euromediterranee del gruppo rugosus (Coleoptera, Meloidae)." volume="20" year="1988">Bologna (1988)</bibRefCitation>
tentatively included 22 species in the 
<taxonomicName genus="E." lsidName="E. brevicollis" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="brevicollis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">E. brevicollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group. However, as this author pointed out, most of these species are very poorly known and, in some cases, the only morphological information on them is from the original description. As a result, the internal taxonomy of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Reitter" authorityYear="1911" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Eurymeloe" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Eurymeloe" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Eurymeloe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
s. str. is very complex and unclear (
<bibRefCitation author="Bologna, MA" journalOrPublisher="Fragmenta Entomologica" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="233 - 301" refId="B1" refString="Bologna, MA, 1988. Note su Eurymeloe e revisione delle specie euromediterranee del gruppo rugosus (Coleoptera, Meloidae). Fragmenta Entomologica 20 (2): 233 - 301" title="Note su Eurymeloe e revisione delle specie euromediterranee del gruppo rugosus (Coleoptera, Meloidae)." volume="20" year="1988">Bologna 1988</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
On the basis of the molecular and morphological data (
<bibRefCitation author="Reitter, E" journalOrPublisher="Catalogus de la entomofauna aragonesa" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" refId="B39" refString="Reitter, E, 1895. Bestimmungs-Tabellen der europaischen Coleopteren Meloidae. I Theil: Meloini. 32. Verlag des Verfassers, Paskau, 1-13." title="Bestimmungs-Tabellen der europaischen Coleopteren Meloidae. I Theil: Meloini. 32. Verlag des Verfassers, Paskau, 1 - 13." year="1895">Reitter 1895</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Reitter, E" journalOrPublisher="Lutz, Stuttgart" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" refId="B40" refString="Reitter, E, 1911. Fauna Germanica. Die Kaefer des Deutschen Reiches. Nach der analytischen Methode bearbeitet. Lutz, Stuttgart" title="Fauna Germanica. Die Kaefer des Deutschen Reiches. Nach der analytischen Methode bearbeitet." year="1911">1911</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.part.13870" author="Escherich, K" journalOrPublisher="Wiener entomologische Zeitung" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="27 - 30" refId="B20" refString="Escherich, K, 1896. Meloiden-studien. IV. Theil. Wiener entomologische Zeitung 15: 27 - 30, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.part.13870" title="Meloiden-studien. IV. Theil." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.part.13870" volume="15" year="1896">Escherich 1896</bibRefCitation>
; 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Martínez">Martinez</normalizedToken>
de la Escalera 1914; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3406/bsef.1926.27653" author="Peyerimhoff, P" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin de la Societe Entomologique de France" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="93 - 96" refId="B34" refString="Peyerimhoff, P, 1926. Meloidae. In: Sainte-Claire Deville J, Peyerimhoff P. Nouveaux Coleopteres du Nord-Africain. Cinquante-cinquieme note. Faune du Grand-Atlas marocain. Bulletin de la Societe Entomologique de France 31 (8): 93 - 96, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3406/bsef.1926.27653" title="Meloidae. In: Sainte-Claire Deville J, Peyerimhoff P. Nouveaux Coleopteres du Nord-Africain. Cinquante-cinquieme note. Faune du Grand-Atlas marocain." url="https://doi.org/10.3406/bsef.1926.27653" volume="31" year="1926">Peyerimhoff 1926</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Bologna, MA" journalOrPublisher="Fragmenta Entomologica" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="233 - 301" refId="B1" refString="Bologna, MA, 1988. Note su Eurymeloe e revisione delle specie euromediterranee del gruppo rugosus (Coleoptera, Meloidae). Fragmenta Entomologica 20 (2): 233 - 301" title="Note su Eurymeloe e revisione delle specie euromediterranee del gruppo rugosus (Coleoptera, Meloidae)." volume="20" year="1988">Bologna 1988</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bologna, MA" journalOrPublisher="Biogeographia" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" refId="B3" refString="Bologna, MA, 1991. Fauna d'Italia. XXVIII. ColeopteraMeloidae. Ed. Calderini, Bologna. [i-xiv] 541 pp." title="Fauna d'Italia. XXVIII. ColeopteraMeloidae. Ed. Calderini, Bologna. [i-xiv] 541 pp." year="1991">1991</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bologna, MA" journalOrPublisher="Miscel-lania Zoologica" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="73 - 80" refId="B4" refString="Bologna, MA, 1994a. Meloidae from Canary and other macaronesian islands (Coleoptera). Miscel-lania Zoologica 16 (1992): 73 - 80" title="Meloidae from Canary and other macaronesian islands (Coleoptera)." volume="16" year="1994 a">1994a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bologna, MA" journalOrPublisher="Miscel-lania Zoologica" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" refId="B5" refString="Bologna, MA, 1994b. I Meloidae della Grecia (Coleoptera). Fragmenta Entomologica 25 (Supplemento): 1-119." title="I Meloidae della Grecia (Coleoptera). Fragmenta Entomologica 25 (Supplemento): 1 - 119." year="1994 b">1994b</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3989/graellsia.2010.v66.018" author="Garcia-Paris, M" journalOrPublisher="Graellsia" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="165 - 212" refId="B22" refString="Garcia-Paris, M, Ruiz, JL, Alonso-Zarazaga, MA, 2010. Catalogo sinonimico de los taxones ibero-baleares de la familia Meloidae (Coleoptera). Graellsia 66 (2): 165 - 212, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3989/graellsia.2010.v66.018" title="Catalogo sinonimico de los taxones ibero-baleares de la familia Meloidae (Coleoptera)." url="https://doi.org/10.3989/graellsia.2010.v66.018" volume="66" year="2010">
<normalizedToken originalValue="García-París">Garcia-Paris</normalizedToken>
et al. 2010
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1080/11250003.2013.776119" author="Di Giulio, A" journalOrPublisher="The Italian Journal of Zoology" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="242 - 254" refId="B17" refString="Di Giulio, A, Sciotti, A, Bologna, MA, 2013. Revision of the first instar larvae of Meloe, subgenera Eurymeloe and Coelomeloe, with new descriptions and a key to the species (Coleoptera: Meloidae). The Italian Journal of Zoology 80 (2): 242 - 254, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1080/11250003.2013.776119" title="Revision of the first instar larvae of Meloe, subgenera Eurymeloe and Coelomeloe, with new descriptions and a key to the species (Coleoptera: Meloidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1080/11250003.2013.776119" volume="80" year="2013">Di Giulio et al. 2013</bibRefCitation>
; this study), we ascribe to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Reitter" authorityYear="1911" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Eurymeloe" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Eurymeloe" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Eurymeloe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
s. str. the following species: 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Eurymeloe" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Eurymeloe (Eurymeloe) algiricus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="algiricus" subGenus="Eurymeloe">Eurymeloe (Eurymeloe) algiricus</taxonomicName>
(Escherich, 1890) (or 
<taxonomicName genus="E." lsidName="E. brevicollis subsp. algiricus" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="subSpecies" species="brevicollis" subSpecies="algiricus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">E. brevicollis algiricus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, see 
<bibRefCitation author="Bologna, MA" editor="Loebl, I" journalOrPublisher="Vol. 5. Tenebrionoidea. Apollo Books, Stenstrup" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="370 - 412" refId="B6" refString="Bologna, MA, 2008. Meloidae. In: Loebl, I, Smetana, A, Eds., Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera. Vol. 5. Tenebrionoidea. Apollo Books, Stenstrup: 370 - 412" title="Meloidae." volumeTitle="Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera." year="2008">Bologna 2008</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName genus="E." lsidName="E. (E.) austrinus" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="austrinus" subGenus="E.">E. (E.) austrinus</taxonomicName>
(Wollaston, 1854), 
<taxonomicName genus="E." lsidName="E. (E.) brevicollis" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="brevicollis" subGenus="E.">E. (E.) brevicollis</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="E." lsidName="E. (E.) corvinus" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="corvinus" subGenus="E.">E. (E.) corvinus</taxonomicName>
(possibly co-specific with the previous species according to 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1080/11250003.2013.776119" author="Di Giulio, A" journalOrPublisher="The Italian Journal of Zoology" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="242 - 254" refId="B17" refString="Di Giulio, A, Sciotti, A, Bologna, MA, 2013. Revision of the first instar larvae of Meloe, subgenera Eurymeloe and Coelomeloe, with new descriptions and a key to the species (Coleoptera: Meloidae). The Italian Journal of Zoology 80 (2): 242 - 254, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1080/11250003.2013.776119" title="Revision of the first instar larvae of Meloe, subgenera Eurymeloe and Coelomeloe, with new descriptions and a key to the species (Coleoptera: Meloidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1080/11250003.2013.776119" volume="80" year="2013">Di Giulio et al. 2013</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName genus="E." lsidName="E. (E.) crosi" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="crosi" subGenus="E.">E. (E.) crosi</taxonomicName>
(Peyerimhoff, 1926), 
<taxonomicName genus="E." lsidName="E. (E.) curticornis" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="curticornis" subGenus="E.">E. (E.) curticornis</taxonomicName>
(
<normalizedToken originalValue="Martínez">Martinez</normalizedToken>
de la Escalera, 1914) (or 
<taxonomicName genus="E." lsidName="E. brevicollis subsp. curticornis" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="subSpecies" species="brevicollis" subSpecies="curticornis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">E. brevicollis curticornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, see 
<bibRefCitation author="Bologna, MA" editor="Loebl, I" journalOrPublisher="Vol. 5. Tenebrionoidea. Apollo Books, Stenstrup" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="370 - 412" refId="B6" refString="Bologna, MA, 2008. Meloidae. In: Loebl, I, Smetana, A, Eds., Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera. Vol. 5. Tenebrionoidea. Apollo Books, Stenstrup: 370 - 412" title="Meloidae." volumeTitle="Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera." year="2008">Bologna 2008</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bologna, MA" editor="Iwan, D" journalOrPublisher="Vol. 5. Tenebrionoidea. Revised and Updated Second Edition, Leiden, Boston, Brill" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="500 - 562" refId="B7" refString="Bologna, MA, 2020a. Meloidae. In: Iwan, D, Loebl, I, Eds., Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera. Vol. 5. Tenebrionoidea. Revised and Updated Second Edition, Leiden, Boston, Brill: 500 - 562" title="Meloidae." volumeTitle="Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera." year="2020 a">2020a</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName genus="E." lsidName="E. (E.) ibericus" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="ibericus" subGenus="E.">E. (E.) ibericus</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName genus="E." lsidName="E. (E.) lederi" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="lederi" subGenus="E.">E. (E.) lederi</taxonomicName>
(Reitter, 1895). The taxonomic positions of 
<taxonomicName genus="E." lsidName="E. luctuosus" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="luctuosus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">E. luctuosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Brandt &amp; Erichson, 1832) (related to 
<taxonomicName genus="E." lsidName="E. crosi" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="crosi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">E. crosi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and 
<taxonomicName genus="E." lsidName="E. scabriusculus" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="scabriusculus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">E. scabriusculus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Brandt &amp; Erichson, 1832) (morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName genus="E." lsidName="E. baudii" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="baudii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">E. baudii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="E." lsidName="E. glazunovi" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="glazunovi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">E. glazunovi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, both now included in 
<taxonomicName family="Meloidae" genus="Bolognaia" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bolognaia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Bolognaia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) are still uncertain (
<bibRefCitation author="Bologna, MA" journalOrPublisher="Fragmenta Entomologica" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="233 - 301" refId="B1" refString="Bologna, MA, 1988. Note su Eurymeloe e revisione delle specie euromediterranee del gruppo rugosus (Coleoptera, Meloidae). Fragmenta Entomologica 20 (2): 233 - 301" title="Note su Eurymeloe e revisione delle specie euromediterranee del gruppo rugosus (Coleoptera, Meloidae)." volume="20" year="1988">Bologna 1988</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bologna, MA" journalOrPublisher="Biogeographia" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" refId="B3" refString="Bologna, MA, 1991. Fauna d'Italia. XXVIII. ColeopteraMeloidae. Ed. Calderini, Bologna. [i-xiv] 541 pp." title="Fauna d'Italia. XXVIII. ColeopteraMeloidae. Ed. Calderini, Bologna. [i-xiv] 541 pp." year="1991">1991</bibRefCitation>
), and their assignment to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Reitter" authorityYear="1911" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Eurymeloe" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Eurymeloe" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Eurymeloe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
s. str. requires further studies.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
Another 13 species [from Palaearctic Asia, except 
<taxonomicName genus="E." lsidName="E. aleuticus" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="aleuticus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">E. aleuticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Borchmann, 1942), from the Aleutian Islands] were provisionally assigned by 
<bibRefCitation author="Bologna, MA" journalOrPublisher="Fragmenta Entomologica" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="233 - 301" refId="B1" refString="Bologna, MA, 1988. Note su Eurymeloe e revisione delle specie euromediterranee del gruppo rugosus (Coleoptera, Meloidae). Fragmenta Entomologica 20 (2): 233 - 301" title="Note su Eurymeloe e revisione delle specie euromediterranee del gruppo rugosus (Coleoptera, Meloidae)." volume="20" year="1988">Bologna (1988)</bibRefCitation>
to the 
<taxonomicName genus="E." lsidName="E. brevicollis" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="brevicollis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">E. brevicollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group: 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Eurymeloe" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Eurymeloe aleuticus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aleuticus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Eurymeloe aleuticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="E." lsidName="E. curticollis" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="curticollis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">E. curticollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Kraatz, 1882), 
<taxonomicName genus="E." lsidName="E. escherichi" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="escherichi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">E. escherichi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Reitter, 1889), 
<taxonomicName genus="E." lsidName="E. frontalis" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="frontalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">E. frontalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Reitter, 1905), 
<taxonomicName genus="E." lsidName="E. gaberti" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="gaberti">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">E. gaberti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Reitter, 1907), 
<taxonomicName genus="E." lsidName="E. laevipennis" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="laevipennis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">E. laevipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Brandt &amp; Erichson, 1832), 
<taxonomicName genus="E." lsidName="E. lobicollis" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="lobicollis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">E. lobicollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fairmaire, 1891), 
<taxonomicName genus="E." lsidName="E. mandli" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="mandli">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">E. mandli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Borchmann, 1942), 
<taxonomicName genus="E." lsidName="E. mathiesseni" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="mathiesseni">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">E. mathiesseni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Reitter, 1905), 
<taxonomicName genus="E." lsidName="E. primulus" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="primulus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">E. primulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Semenow, 1903), 
<taxonomicName genus="E." lsidName="E. servulus" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="servulus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">E. servulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Bates, 1879), 
<taxonomicName genus="E." lsidName="E. transversicollis" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="transversicollis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">E. transversicollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fairmaire, 1891), and 
<taxonomicName genus="E." lsidName="E. zolotarevi" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="zolotarevi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">E. zolotarevi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Pliginskij, 1914). As in the previous case, additional molecular and morphological studies are required to determine the subgeneric assignment of these species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
Regarding other species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Reitter" authorityYear="1911" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Eurymeloe" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Eurymeloe" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Eurymeloe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.23885/1814-3326-2012-8-2-205-210" author="Shapovalov, AM" journalOrPublisher="Caucasian Entomological Bulletin" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="205 - 210" refId="B54" refString="Shapovalov, AM, 2012. A new species of the Eurymeloe Reitter, 1911 (Coleoptera, Meloidae: Meloe) from the steppe zone of Russia and Kazakhstan. Caucasian Entomological Bulletin 8 (2): 205 - 210, DOI: https://doi.org/10.23885/1814-3326-2012-8-2-205-210" title="A new species of the Eurymeloe Reitter, 1911 (Coleoptera, Meloidae: Meloe) from the steppe zone of Russia and Kazakhstan." url="https://doi.org/10.23885/1814-3326-2012-8-2-205-210" volume="8" year="2012">Shapovalov (2012)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shapovalov" authorityYear="2012" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Meloe" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Meloe (Eurymeloe) sarmaticus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sarmaticus" subGenus="Eurymeloe">Meloe (Eurymeloe) sarmaticus</taxonomicName>
Shapovalov, 2012 from Russia and Central Kazakhstan and considered it closely related to the Russian-Kazakh 
<taxonomicName genus="E." lsidName="E. aeneus" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="aeneus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">E. aeneus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Tauscher, 1812). The last species, together with 
<taxonomicName genus="E." lsidName="E. pusio" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="pusio">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">E. pusio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Wellman, 1910) and 
<taxonomicName genus="E." lsidName="E. asperatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="asperatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">E. asperatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Tan, 1981), were considered 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">incertae sedis</emphasis>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Bologna, MA" journalOrPublisher="Fragmenta Entomologica" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="233 - 301" refId="B1" refString="Bologna, MA, 1988. Note su Eurymeloe e revisione delle specie euromediterranee del gruppo rugosus (Coleoptera, Meloidae). Fragmenta Entomologica 20 (2): 233 - 301" title="Note su Eurymeloe e revisione delle specie euromediterranee del gruppo rugosus (Coleoptera, Meloidae)." volume="20" year="1988">Bologna (1988)</bibRefCitation>
. However, recently, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bologna, MA" editor="Iwan, D" journalOrPublisher="Vol. 5. Tenebrionoidea. Revised and Updated Second Edition, Leiden, Boston, Brill" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="500 - 562" refId="B7" refString="Bologna, MA, 2020a. Meloidae. In: Iwan, D, Loebl, I, Eds., Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera. Vol. 5. Tenebrionoidea. Revised and Updated Second Edition, Leiden, Boston, Brill: 500 - 562" title="Meloidae." volumeTitle="Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera." year="2020 a">Bologna (2020a)</bibRefCitation>
integrated them into 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Reitter" authorityYear="1911" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Eurymeloe" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Eurymeloe" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Eurymeloe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(at the subgenus level), although he still considers 
<taxonomicName genus="E." lsidName="E. aeneus" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="aeneus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">E. aeneus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
a doubtful ascription. We did not examine material of these species; therefore, we cannot add new information on their current taxonomic placement.
</paragraph>
